Valdir Benedito (born October 25, 1965 in Araraquara, Brazil) is a retired Brazilian football player who played for Atltico Paranaense (Brazil), Atltico Mineiro (Brazil), Cruzeiro (Brazil), Internacional (Brazil) and Kashiwa Reysol (Japan). He was a participant at 1991 Copa Amrica in Chile and capped 3 times for the Brazilian national team between 1991. [1] 
